<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Lone Wolf,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mate Sought For Lonely West German Wolf</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ARNSBERG, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mate is being sought for a lonely
wolf that a local official says is in danger of dying of a broken
heart.
   Arnsberg administrator Richard Gruenschlaeger on Wednesday asked
residents to help find a young female mate for a North American
timber wolf recently found caged in the city.
   Authorities took the wolf to a nearby zoo, but he remains
isolated because other wolves would attack a newcomer,
Gruenschlaeger said.
   ``Timber wolves have a very strong need to live within a
community,'' Gruenschlaeger said. ``He is destined to die without
company.''
   Gruenschlaeger said the wolf could not be returned to the wild
because he had spent too long in a cage.
   ``His only hope is to find a pretty young female wolf with whom
he can build his own pack,'' Gruenschlaeger said.
</TEXT>
