<1ST_LINE>r i PM-747Crashes     12-22 0211</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-747 Crashes,0217</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>List of Boeing 747 Crashes</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Britain-Crash, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of some of the worst commercial aviation disasters
involving Boeing 747s:
   Nov. 28, 1987: 160 are killed when a South African Airways 747
crashes off the island of Mauritius in the Indian Ocean.
   Aug. 12, 1985: In the worst single-plane accident, 520 people are
killed when a Japan Airlines Boeing 747 crashes into a mountain on a
domestic flight.
   June 23, 1985: All 329 people aboard die when an Air India Boeing
747 crashes off the coast of Ireland. Investigators attributed the
crash to a terrorist-planted bomb.
   On Nov. 27, 1983: 183 killed are when an Avianca Boeing 747
crashes near Madrid's Barajas airport.
   Sept. 1, 1983: A Korean Air Lines 747 is shot down by a Soviet
fighter after flying through Soviet airspace near Sakhalin Island.
All 269 people aboard are killed.
   Jan. 1, 1978: 213 die when an Air Indian 747 en route to the
Middle East kingdom of Dubai crashes less than two minutes after
taking off from Bombay.
   March 27, 1977: 582 people are killed in a collision of two
Boeing 747s operated by Pan American and KLM at the airport on
Tenerife in Spain's Canary Islands.
</TEXT>
