<HEAD>Dollar Up In Tokyo, Stocks Also Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar firmed against the Japanese yen Thursday,
while stock prices also rose marginally.
   The dollar closed at 124.62 yen, up 0.40 yen from Wednesday's
close. It opened at 124.35 yen and ranged between 124.30 yen and
124.80 yen.
   Currency traders said the dollar came under downward pressure in
early dealings in Sydney but quickly regained stability, affecting
the Tokyo market.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues rose by 76.42 points, or 0.26 percent, from the
previous day, closing at 29,774.61. It had climbed by 130.25 points
on Wednesday.
   Stock dealers said many investors were merely fine tuning their
positions with a prevailing wait-and-see mood in preparation for the
year-end holiday market closings.
