<HEAD>Dollar And Stocks Both Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar firmed against the Japanese yen in slow
pre-holiday trading today, while stock prices also rose marginally.
   The dollar closed at 124.62, up 0.40 yen from Wednesday's close.
It opened at 124.35 yen and ranged between 124.30 yen and 124.80 yen.
   An official of the Bank of Tokyo, who spoke on condition of
