   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues rose by 76.42 points, or 0.26 percent, from the
previous day, closing at 29,774.61. The index had gained 130.25
points on Wednesday.
   On the stock market, dealers said many investors were merely fine
tuning their positions with a wait-and-see mood prevailing before
Japan's yearend holidays.
