<HEAD>Thief Steals Car With 224 Dozen Cookies in Trunk</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A thief who swiped a car from a driveway got a
bonus of enough home-made cookies for a Texas-size Christmas party,
but the sweets may not be worth it since they were intended for the
sheriff's department.
   Cynthia Gammill said there were 224 dozen cookies in the trunk of
her stolen car. They were baked by members of the First United
Methodist Church of Dallas for members of the Dallas County
sheriff's office who have to work Christmas.
   When the women found out there would be 600 people working on the
holiday, they began baking the 2,688 cookies right after
Thanksgiving.
   Sheriff's department spokesman Jim Ewell said he hopes the
thieves will discover the cookies and realize they were destined for
lawmen and abandon the car because ``they don't want to deal with
it.''
   The women are back to their ovens.
   ``They all said they are willing to bake another two dozen by
Friday,'' Ms. Gammill said.
