<HEAD>Soldier Dies Of Wounds, 13 Arabs Wounded</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RONI RABIN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Israeli soldier who was critically injured
when he tried to rescue a woman from a passenger bus that was
firebombed in the West Bank died today in a London hospital, the
army said.
   Also today, troops shot and wounded 13 Palestinians in sporadic
clashes in the occupied territories, Arab hospital officials and
reporters said.
   Military spokesmen said they could not immediately confirm the
casualties in today's violence and were checking the reports.
   The soldier's death raised to 14 the number of Israelis who have
died in the yearlong Palestinian revolt against Israeli occupation
of the West Bank and Gaza Strip. At least 333 Palestinians have died.
   The army identified the soldier as 19-year-old David Deloroza of
Jerusalem. He was transferred to a London hospital for an operation
to replace his heart and lungs, which were severely damaged from
smoke inhalation during the firebomb attack near the city of Jericho.
   Palestinian guerrillas hurled the bombs at the Israeli bus on
Oct. 31. Deloroza tried to save Rachel Weiss, an Israeli woman who
refused to leave the burning bus without her children. She and the
three children burned to death.
   In Bethlehem, activists belonging to a Palestinian Communist
faction today painted slogans on the walls in red warning Christians
to abide by a general strike called for Christmas Eve.
   ``Remain home on Dec. 24,'' one slogan read.
   ``No Christmas celebrations .... Only prayers,'' said another.
   In the West Bank's largest city of Nablus, Palestinian protesters
took to the streets after a curfew was lifted early today. Five
people were wounded in clashes with troops, including a 42-year-old
woman shot in the arm, local reporters and hospital officials said.
   In the occupied Gaza Strip, seven Palestinians were shot and
wounded, including a 9-year-old boy shot in the abdomen, Arab
doctors said.
   Also today, one man was shot and wounded in the southern West
Bank city of Hebron, hospital officials said.
</TEXT>
