by Yasser Arafat. He spoke after meeting with Foreign Minister Esmat
Abdel-Meguid.
   In Washington, a U.S. government source said the U.S. Embassy in
Helsinki, Finland, received a telephone threat about two weeks ago
from a person claiming to belong to the Abu Nidal group, a radical
Palestinian faction that has been implicated in terrorist attacks.
   The caller said a bomb would be placed aboard a Pan Am plane and
that it would be carried by a woman, said the government source, who
spoke on condition of anonymity.
   Arafat publicly renounced terrorism last week and accepted other
U.S. conditions, leading Washington to open a dialogue with the PLO
after a 13-year ban on contacts with the group.
