<HEAD>Man Sings Carols While Fleeing Holdup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A robber sang Christmas carols after stealing
more than $1,000 from a bank teller who was carrying the cash from
one bank to another, police said.
   The teller was accosted Wednesday by a neatly dressed man who
pulled his shirt up to display a .25-caliber pistol, police said. He
snatched the bag of money from her hand and fled, singing Christmas
carols as he left.
   ``I don't know what the carols were,'' said police spokeswoman
Carmine Menschel. ``Believe me, I asked.''
   Menschel would not identify the teller.
