<1ST_LINE>u i PM-Italy-BombThreat     12-22 0156</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Italy-Bomb Threat,0159</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Plane Makes Unscheduled Stop After Bomb Threat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A British Airways Tristar made an unscheduled stop in
Rome today after an anonymous caller said a bomb had been planted on
board, officials said.
   Authorities closed Rome's main Leonardo da Vinci airport for 20
minutes while the passengers disembarked and the plane was moved to
an isolated area, where the aircraft and the luggage were examined.
   Flight 146 originated in New Delhi and stopped in Kuwait before
heading toward its destination, London, said Carla Rossi, a British
Airways employee at the Rome airport. It landed at Rome at about 4
p.m.
   The plane was carrying 242 people.
   Ms. Rossi said someone had called the airline's London office and
said a bomb was on board the aircraft.
   On Wednesday night, a Pan Am Boeing 747 flying from London to New
York crashed in a Scottish village, killing all 259 passengers and
crew.
</TEXT>
