<1ST_LINE>r a PM-PiggyBankThief     12-22 0190</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Piggy Bank Thief,0193</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Piggy Bank Theft Worth Nine Years In Jail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A burglar who stole an old plastic
piggy bank stuffed with $75 in change has been sentenced to nine
years in prison.
   Palm Beach Circuit Judge Howard Berman cited Henry Hatten's
previous felony convictions before issuing the sentence Wednesday,
ending a trial in which jurors giggled when prosecutors introduced
the piggy bank as evidence.
   ``If you have to be broken into, this is the guy to have,'' said
piggy bank owner Sylvia Jones of Riviera Beach. ``He's very neat, he
doesn't trash the place and he only takes a piggy bank. I don't know
if he's extremely bright if that's all he stole.''
   Hatten took the bank July 15, three weeks after completing his
fourth prison sentence in 10 years. Ms. Jones said she bought the
little bank for her son's savings after he was born, almost 32 years
ago.
   But the bank remains in state custody and Ms. Jones wants to
bring home the bacon.
   ``I definitely want it back,'' she said. ``It's been in the
family almost 32 years.''
</TEXT>
