<HEAD>13 Injured In Grenade Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A grenade exploded near a group
of people standing next to a police station near Cape Town, injuring
13 people, including 10 policemen, authorities said.
   Two children and one woman were hurt in the attack Wednesday,
police said.
   Police said the grenade was tossed from a moving vehicle in
Nyanga township, about 10 miles outside Cape Town. They did not give
the races of the victims, but most policemen in the township are
black.
   Militant anti-apartheid activists consider black policemen to be
collaborators with the white-led government and frequently target
them for attack.
   No one claimed responsibility for the attack, but police have
blamed most such incidents on the outlawed African National Congress
guerrilla movement.
</TEXT>
