<HEAD>Woman Enters Burning Home, Dies For Dogs</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: RESTORES dropped words in lede</NOTE>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman died of injuries suffered when she went
back into her burning home Dec. 3 in a failed attempt to save her
two pet beagles.
   Mae J. Stapp, 67, died at Mercy Hospital on Wednesday of burns
over 52 percent of her body. Hardening of the arteries and diabetes
contributed to her death, said James Gregris, chief deputy coroner
for Allegheny County.
   ``According to the nephew, she wasn't burned or injured when he
took her out of the house the first time. She was safe, but couldn't
leave the dogs inside,'' said fire Capt. John Bauer. ``She tried to
save their lives and lost her own.''
   The dogs were found in the rubble of the home.
