<HEAD>Spanish Painter Salvador Dali In Hospital</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: LEADS throughout with new information and background.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>FIGUERAS, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Spanish painter Salvador Dali was admitted
to the emergency unit of a hospital Thursday night suffering from a
stomach hemorrhage and was under medical observation, a hospital
official said.
   The 84-year-old Surrealist painter was being attended by four
doctors at Figueras Hospital, said the hospital's admissions clerk,
who refused to be identified.
   The clerk said the physicians expected to report on Dali's
condition Friday.
   Dali lives at his Galatea Tower mansion in Figueras, a town 60
miles north of Barcelona, the seaside provincial capital in
northeastern Spain.
   He had returned to his home Dec. 14 after spending 16 days
hospitalized in Figueras and Barcelona, being treated for a severe
heart problem aggravated by blood clots in the lung.
   Dali's ``Persistence of Memory'' _ with its limp watches and
barren landscape _ is perhaps the most celebrated Surrealist
painting.
</TEXT>
