   SEPT. 17 _ Summer Olympics open in Seoul.
   SEPT. 29 _ Shuttle Discovery launched, resuming U.S. manned space
program.
   OCT. 1 _ In major shakeup, Gorbachev becomes Soviet president,
Gromyko retires.
   OCT. 3 _ Beirut hostage Mithileshwar Singh, U.S. resident, freed.
   OCT. 5 _ President Pinochet loses Chilean referendum.
   OCT. 19-25 _ Hurricane Joan kills 184 in Central America.
   OCT. 20 _ Dodgers defeat Oakland A's to win World Series.
   OCT. 21 _ Deposed Philippine President Ferdinand Marcos and wife,
Imelda, indicted on racketeering charges in New York.
