<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
247,788 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
260,816, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is higher than the same week a year ago,
in which 127,072 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 165,314 cars this week,
compared with 168,519 a week ago and 75,065 in the same week in 1987.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 82,474,
compared with last week's 92,297 and last year's 52,007.
   Canadian automakers were to build 17,181 cars this week, down
from 18,380 a week ago but up from last year's 14,151.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 19,756, compared
with 21,547 a week ago and 11,195 in the same week last year.
