<2ND_LINE>AM-Coca-Cola-Stock,0195</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Coca-Cola Enterprises Announces Details Of Stock Repurchase Program</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Coca-Cola Enterprises said Thursday it would buy
back 5.3 million of its shares by the end of the year.
   The Coca-Cola Co. bottling subsidiary, which has already
repurchased 2.5 million shares from the public in 1988, said in a
statement it intends to buy the 5.3 million shares from its parent
company before the end of 1988.
   Coca-Cola Enterprises stock closed at $14.62{ a share in New York
Stock Exchange trading Wednesday. At that price, the buyback would
cost the company $77.5 million.
   The stock repurchase is part of a buyback of 25 million shares
that Coca-Cola Enterprises plans to finish by the end of 1990.
   Coca-Cola Enterprises said it plans to repurchase approximately
13 million shares from Coca-Cola Co. and approximately 12 million
shares from public shareholders over the course of the repurchase
program, which has the goal of adjusting Coca-Cola Co. ownership to
49 percent.
   Coca-Cola Enterprises also announced Thursday it completed the
sale of The Coca-Cola Bottling Company of Mid-America to the
Johnston Coca-Cola Bottling Group Inc. on Dec. 16.
</TEXT>
