<HEAD>AT&T Announces Acquisition Of Eaton Financial Corp.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MORRISTOWN, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eaton Financial Corp. of Framingham,
Mass., will become a wholly-owned subsidiary of AT&T Credit Corp.
under a $70 million stock swap merger agreement announced Thursday.
   Under the definitive agreement approved by the Eaton's board of
directors, the Eaton stock would be converted into a fraction of a
share of AT&T common stock, according to an AT&T news release.
   The merger is subject to approvals by regulators and Eaton
shareholders.
   ``Joining with AT&T Credit Corporation provides Eaton Financial
Corporation with the potential to enhance our competitive postion in
the marketplace and continue our rapid growth which will enable us
to offer a total equipment financing program unsurpassed in the
industry,'' said Judith Gass, executive vice president of Eaton.
   AT&T Credit Corp., based in Morristown, is a financing company
owned by American Telephone & Telegraph Co. Eaton specializes in
leasing small ticket office and business equipment to commercial
users nationwide, the news release said.
</TEXT>
